      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ASTON FLAMENCO (7) hit the ground running off the tricky draw and gave a sight in front, boxing on well for a minor when second (22.54) at this track in a T3 Grade 6 over 390m. Overdue and expected to feature again. NALA'S MANTIS (1) has been beaten for early speed lately, last time finishing sixth (24.64) in a T3 RSTW at Bendigo. Goes well out of this box with a win and three minor placings. Key player if finds best. PRESENCE (6) doesn't win out of turn but recent form sound. Filled a minor placings again last time when second (22.53) at Shepparton making it three placings in a row. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. Deserves a win and gets her chance. CAVED IN (8) was a shock winner last start and is in the mix again.",
